### Numbered

Now you can skip using `vars()` and the named column and just supply the column number. This is a great usecase if you have a lot of columns that need to be used and want a low-effort way of indicating.

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
temps %>% 
  gt() %>% 
  data_color(
    columns = 2:13,
    colors = hulk_pal
  )
```

