### Names

You can subset the names of the column but without using `tidyeval` must assign it to an object to use it inside `vars()`.

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
cols_affect <- names(temps)[2:13]

temps %>% 
  gt() %>% 
  data_color(
    columns = vars(cols_affect),
    colors = hulk_pal
  )
```

