#### Names + `!!!`

If you use `tidyeval`'s bang-bang-bang operator (`!!!`), then you can parse the R code inside the `vars()` call.

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
temps %>% 
  gt() %>% 
  data_color(
    columns = vars(!!!names(temps)[2:13]),
    colors = hulk_pal
  )
```

