#### Strings + `c()`

IF you use a `c()` you need to use the `!!!` operator. More details at [Advanced R](https://adv-r.hadley.nz/quasiquotation.html).

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
temps %>% 
  gt() %>% 
  data_color(
    columns = vars(!!!c("Jan", "Feb")),
    colors = hulk_pal
  )
```

